    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5877" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λυγρός</span></b>  (cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λευγαλέος</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">sad, mournful,
            miserable;</span> in apparently active sense, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">φάρμακα, σήματα</span>, etc., <i><span class="en">Od.
            4.230</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 6.168</span></i>; also fig.,
          and in derogatory sense, ‘sorry,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εἵματα</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 16.457</span></i>; so
          of persons, <i><span class="en">Il. 13.119</span></i>.—Adv.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λυγρῶς</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
